Morse Code Converter GUI (with Audio Playback)

A Python GUI application that converts text to Morse Code and vice versa. It also plays Morse Code using sound beeps and includes an easy-to-use interface built with Tkinter.

Features

Convert English text to Morse Code

Convert Morse Code to English text

Play Morse Code with dot and dash sounds using pygame

Copy the output to the clipboard with one click

User-friendly interface built using Tkinter


How to Use

Run the script to open the GUI window

Enter either plain text or Morse Code in the input field

Click:

"Convert to Morse" – to encode text

"Convert to Text" – to decode Morse

"Play Morse Code" – to hear audio beeps

"Copy to Clipboard" – to copy the output



Note: In Morse Code, use / to represent space between words

Getting Started

Prerequisites

Python 3.x

pygame library installed


Installation

1. Clone the repository:

git clone https://github.com/Nirmal2509/Text-to-Morse-Code-Converter-GUI.git
cd Text-to-Morse-Code-Converter-GUI


2. Install dependencies:

pip install pygame


3. Make sure dot.wav and dash.wav files are in the same folder



Run the App

python morse_converter.py

File Structure

Text-to-Morse-Code-Converter-GUI/
├── morse_converter.py     # Main Python script
├── dot.wav                # Sound for dot (.)
├── dash.wav               # Sound for dash (-)
└── README.md              # Project documentation

Code Overview

text_to_morse() – Converts text to Morse Code

morse_to_text() – Converts Morse Code to text

play_morse() – Plays Morse Code using sound

copy_to_clipboard() – Copies the output to the clipboard

Tkinter GUI layout and buttons for interaction


Demo

Input: HELLO
Output: .... . .-.. .-.. ---
Play: Dots and dashes play as sound beeps

